Intesa, Parmalat, Telecom Italia: Italian Equity Preview

-- B y   A l e s s a n d r a   M i g l i a c c i o
-- 
2011-05-23T04:03:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/intesa-parmalat-telecom-italia-italian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close.  Italy ’s benchmark FTSE MIB Index fell 322.85, or 1.5
percent, to 21,236.87 in Milan.  Indesit SpA (IND IM): The Italian maker of stoves and
refrigerators has up to 700 million euros ($994 million)
available for acquisitions as part of a plan to gain market
share in Europe, Il Sole 24 Ore  reported , citing Chief Executive
Officer Marco Milani. Indesit lost 2.4 percent to 7.79 euros.        Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP)  : Italy’s second-biggest bank
will start selling new shares at 1.369 euros each and offer 2
common shares for every 7 common savings shares held, in a 5
billion-euro offer aimed at strengthening its finances. Shares
fell 3.6 percent to 1.94 euros.  Parmalat SpA (PLT)  : Groupe Lactalis’ 2.6 euro-a-share
offer for stock it doesn’t already own in Parmalat opens today.
Italy’s biggest dairy company said May 20 Lactalis’ valuation is
too low and the company may be worth as much as 3.17 euros-a-
share, according to Goldman Sachs Group Inc. Shares declined 0.8
percent to 2.60 euros.  Telecom Italia SpA (TIT)  : Italy’s biggest phone
company’s Brazilian unit, Tim Brasil, is interested in buying
 Aes Atimus , a Brazilian fiber optics grid company, La Repubblica
 reported , without saying where it got the information. Shares
declined 0.6 percent to 0.99 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alessandra Migliaccio in Rome at 
